headline.0: Hopes of Religious Freedom in Former Soviet Union Fall Short
headline.1: Hopes of Religious Freedom in Former Soviet Union Fall Short
headline.2: Demonstrators Block Road To Donald Trump Rally In Arizona

short_description.0: Vladimir Putin's lock on Russia's leadership since 2000 has given the Russian Orthodox Church an even more commanding position in the country's religious picture. Putin has publicly called the church, which he attends, a vital part of Russian life and tradition.
